        "title": "Add development trace UI",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a source-checkout-only development LLM trace recorder for full prompt/tool payload debugging.\n- Exposes `traces.capabilities`, `traces.list`, and `traces.get` Gateway methods behind explicit development flags, admin scope, and a strict direct-loopback Control UI grant.\n- Bridges Codex app-server turns into the dev trace store so local debugging shows the actual turn/start payload, available tools, streamed/final response events, and timing/byte metadata.\n- Adds a Phoenix-style Traces Control UI with a compact trace selector and a dominant detail pane for prompt messages, tool schemas/arguments, parameters, response text, and raw payload disclosures.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts -t \"fires llm_input, llm_output, and agent_end hooks for codex turns\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/styles/components.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.ts ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts src/plugin-sdk/diagnostic-runtime.ts src/infra/llm-dev-tracing.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts ui/src/styles/components.css ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Development-only tracing UI shows captured LLM prompt payloads, tool schemas, invocation parameters, response events, and raw request/response JSON while remaining disabled outside an explicit source-checkout loopback debugging session.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Control UI Playwright/Chromium E2E server with mocked Gateway WebSocket responses, plus a local Gateway dashboard run with `OPENCLAW_DEV_TRACING_UI=1`, `OPENCLAW_DEV_TRACE_LLM_PAYLOADS=1`, and `OPENCLAW_DEV_TRACE_LLM_RESPONSE=1`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Captured a Playwright browser recording through the Traces route with mock trace capability enabled; then ran a real local Codex dashboard prompt and verified the generated `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` trace appeared in `/traces` with prompt, tools, response, raw request, raw response, concrete TTFB, and a wider detail pane than selector.\n\nEvidence after fix: Mocked visual proof is in `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/tracing-ui-selector-polish/` (`desktop-readable.png`, `desktop-raw-expanded.png`, `tracing-ui-selector-polish.webm`, `selector-polish-proof.json`). Live local Codex trace proof is in `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/tracing-ui-live/` (`codex-chat-response.png`, `codex-trace-readable.png`, `codex-trace-raw-expanded.png`, `codex-trace-live.webm`, `codex-trace-proof.json`). The refreshed selector proof reports `detailWiderThanList: true`, `horizontalOverflow: false`, `promptVisible: true`, `rawRequestVisible: true`, `rowHasDuration: false`, `rowHasRequestBytes: false`, and `toolSchemaVisible: true`.\n\nObserved result after fix: The Traces tab renders a compact left selector containing model/status/call/tool count only, while the detail pane owns the readable prompt, tool, parameter, response, and raw JSON sections. The live Codex run produced a trace from the app-server bridge and the trace UI exposed the full turn/start payload without showing the metadata-heavy timing/size row in the selector.\n\nWhat was not tested: A completed local autoreview run; the autoreview subprocess stalled with no output after more than 14 minutes, so the final bridge/UI diff received a manual focused review instead. `agent-browser record` was also unavailable because `ffmpeg` is not installed, so the recording artifact uses Playwright `recordVideo`.\n",
